GridGameLauncherc.exe works for me, although sometimes it'll give me a "Securom Faild to Load" error, but it'll load fine right after. 
But once you get the cracked game loaded there's a simple way around it asking for a key in-game (which it does for me); just exit the Activation Key window. My GFWL is setup to auto-login to my Offline account, and despite the game asking for a key every time I load it, it still logs in to my Offline account. After you're out of that part you can go make an Offline account or just login if you've already got one. Game saves fine, no other problems noticed.

